data.name: uReserved7_6
description: Reserved

data.name: uVidStd
description: Sets the input video standard mode. Configuration is dependant on
PRIM_MODE[3:0]. Setting appropriate mode is important to get Free Run mode
working.

data.name: uReserved7
description: Reserved

data.name: uVFreq
description: A control to set vertical frequency.

data.name: uPrimMode
description: A control to selects the primary mode of operation of the decoder. Setting
appropriate HDMI mode is important to get FreeRun mode working. To be used
with VID_STD[5:0]

data.name: uInpColorSpace
description: A control to set the colorspace of the input video. To be used in conjunction
with ALT_GAMMA and RGB_OUT to configure the color space converter. A value of
4'b1111 selects automatic setting of the input color space base on the primary
mode and video standard settings. Settings 1000 to 1110 are undefined.

values.description: Forces YCrCb input (601 color space) (range 16 to 235).
Forces YCrCb input (709 color space) (range 16 to 235).
Forces YCrCb input (601 color space) (range 0 to 255).
Forces YCrCb input (601 color space) (range 0 to 255).
Forces YCrCb input (709 color space) (range 0 to 255).
Input color space depends on color space reported by HDMI block.

data.name: uAltGamma
description: A control to set the colorspace of the input video. To be used in conjunction
with ALT_GAMMA and RGB_OUT to configure the color space converter. A value of
4'b1111 selects automatic setting of the input color space base on the primary
mode and video standard settings. Settings 1000 to 1110 are undefined.

values.description: YUV601 to YUV709 conversion applied if input is YUV601. YUV709 to YUV601 conversion applied if input is YUV709.

data.name: uOp656Range
description: A control to set the output range of the digital data. It also automatically
the data saturator setting.

data.name: uRgbOut
description: A control to select output color space and the correct digital blank level and
offsets on the RGB or YPrPb outputs. It is used in conjunction with the
INP_COLOR_SPACE[3:0] and ALT_GAMMA bits to select the applied CSC.

data.name: uAltDataSat
description: A control to disable the data saturator that limits the output range
independently of OP_656_RANGE. This bit is used to support extended data range
modes.

values.description: Data saturator enabled or disabled according to OP_656_RANGE setting.
Reverses OP_656_RANGE decision to enable or disable the data saturator.

data.name: uOpFormatSel
description: A control to select the data format and pixel bus configuration. Refer to the pixel port
configuration for full information on pixel port modes and configuration settings

data.name: uOpChSel
description: A control to select the configuration of the pixel data bus on the pixel pins. Refer to
the pixel port configuration for full information on pixel port modes and configuration
settings..

data.name: uReserved4_3
description: Reserved

data.name: uXtalFreqSel
description: A control to set the XTAL frequency used

data.name: uReserved0
description: Reserved

data.name: uReserved7_5
description: Reserved.

data.name: uFOutSel
description: A control to select DE signal or Field signal to be output on the FIELD/DE pin.

data.name: uDataBlankEn
description: A control to blank data during video blanking sections.

values.description: Do not blank data during horizontal and vertical blanking periods.
Blank data during horizontal and vertical blanking periods.

data.name: uAvcodeInsertEn
description: A control to select AV code insertion into the data stream.

values.description: Does not insert AV codes into data stream.
Inserts AV codes into data stream.

data.name: uReplAvCode
description: A control to select the duplication of the AV codes and insertion on all data channels of
the output data stream.
Outputs complete SAV/EAV codes on all Channels, Channel A, Channel B and Channel C.
Spreads AV code across the three channels. Channel B and Channel C contain the
first two ten bit words, 0x3FF and 0x000. Channel A contains the final two ten bit
words 0x00 and 0xXYZ.

data.name: uOpSwapCbCr
description: A controls the swapping of Cr and Cb data on the pixel buses.
Outputs Cr and Cb as per OP_FORMAT_SEL.
Inverts the order of Cb and Cr in the interleaved data stream.

data.name: uVsOutSel
description: A control to select VSync signal or Field signal to be output on VS/Field pin.

data.name: uReserved6_4
description: Reserved.

data.name: uInvFPol
description: A control to select the polarity of FIELD/DE signal.

data.name: uInvVsPol
description: A control to select the polarity of VS/FIELD signal.

data.name: uInvHsPol
description: A control to select the polarity of HS signal.

data.name: uInvLlcPol
description: A control to select the polarity of the LLC.

data.name: uReserved7_2
description: Reserved.

data.name: uCorePdn
description: A power-down control for the DPP, CP core and digital sections of the HDMI core.

values.description: Powers up CP and digital sections of HDMI block.
Powers down the CP and digital section of HDMI block.

data.name: uXtalPdn
description: A power-down control for the XTAL in the digital blocks.

values.description: Powers up XTAL buffer to the digital core.
Powers down XTAL buffer to the digital core.

data.name: uReserved7_6
description: Reserved.

data.name: uPowerDown
description: A control to enable power-down mode. This is the main I2C power-down control.

data.name: uReserved4_3
description: Reserved.

data.name: uCpPwrdn
description: A power-down control for the CP core.

values.description: Powers up the clock to the CP core.
Powers down the clock to the CP core. HDMI block will not be affected by this bit.

data.name: uReserved1
description: Reserved.

data.name: uPadsPdn
description: A power down control for pads of the digital output pins. When enabled pads are tristated
and the input path is disabled. This control applies to the DE, HS, VS, INT, LLC pads and
the pixel pads P0 to P47.

values.description: Powers up the pads of the digital output pins.
Powers down the pads of the digital output pins.

data.name: uReserved7_5
description: Reserved.

data.name: uCpStdiInterlaced
description: A readback to indicate the interlaced status of the currently selected STDI block applied
to the CP core.

values.description: Selected STDI has detected a progressive input.
Selected STDI has detected a interlaced input.

data.name: uCpInterlaced
description: A readback to indicate the interlaced status of the CP core based on configuration of
Video standard and INTERLACED bit in the CP map.

values.description: CP core is processing the input as a progressive input.
CP core is processing the input as a interlaced input.

data.name: uCpProgParmForInt
description: A readback to indicate the if the CP core is processing for progressive standard while are
the Video standard and the INTERLACED bit in the CP Map are configured for an interlaced
standard.
CP core processing for a progressive standard while Video standard and the
INTERLACED bits are configured for an interlaced standard.
CP core processing for a progressive standard while Video standard and the
INTERLACED bits are configured for an progressive standard

data.name: uCpForceInterlaced
description: A readback to indicate forced-interlaced status of the CP core based on configuration of
Video standard and INTERLACED bit in the CP Map..
Input is detected as interlaced and the CP is programmed in an interlaced mode via
VID_STD[5:0].
Input is detected as progressive and the CP is programmed in an interlaced mode

data.name: uCpNonStdVideo
description: A control to indicate that the CP core has detected a non standard number of lines on the
incoming video compared to the standard specified by VID_STD[5:0]
Input has same number of lines as that of the format programmed.
Input has different number of lines to that of format programmed

data.name: uReserved7_6
description: Reserved.

data.name: uDrStr
description: A control to set the drive strength of the data output drivers.
Medium low(2 x).
Medium high(3 x)
High(4 x)

data.name: uDrStrClk
description: A control to set the drive strength control for the output pixel clock out signal on the LLC pin.
Medium low(2 x) for LLC up to 60 MHz.
Medium high(3 x) for LLC from 44 MHz to 105 MHz.
High(4 x) for LLC greater than 100 MHz.

data.name: uDrStrSync
description: A control to set the drive strength the synchronization pins, HS, VS and DE.
Medium low(2 x).
Medium high(3 x).
High(4 x).

data.name: uReserved7_5
description: Reserved

data.name: uTriAudio
description: A control to tristate the audio output interface pins (AP0, AP1/I2S_TDM, AP2 ... AP5).
Audio output pins active.
Tristate audio output pins.

data.name: uTriSyncs
description: Synchronization output pins tristate control. The synchronization pins under this control
are HS, VS and DE.
Sync output pins active.
Tristate sync output pins.

data.name: uTriLlc
description: A control to tristate the output pixel clock on the LLC pin.
LLC pin active.
Tristate LLC pin.

data.name: uTriPix
description: A control to tristate the pixel data on the pixel pins P[47:0].
Pixel bus active.
Tristate pixel bus.

data.name: uReserved0
description: Reserved.
